I"<p>In a rare situation, bullet points and numbers for a list may not look good in certain style; so here is a solution on how to remove those default styles for a list.</p>

<p>With the following code, you can remove the numbers, bullet points, and indentation for lists.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-css" data-lang="css"><span class="nt">ul</span> <span class="p">{</span>
  <span class="nl">list-style-type</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="nb">none</span><span class="p">;</span>
  <span class="nl">margin-left</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">0px</span><span class="p">;</span>
  <span class="nl">padding-left</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">0px</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="p">}</span></code></pre></figure>

